programmes.show_description: For Better Or A Lot Worse. The first couple to ever take on the challenge test their survival skills and relationship. They face jaguars, anacondas and caiman in the Guyana jungle. S5, Ep12
Feel The Burn. Two superfans battle oppressive heat and relentless insect attacks in Guyana's scorching savanna. Severe dehydration forces a desperate fan to drink unsanitary fluids. S5, Ep13

C&O Railway. The team travels to Clifton Forge, to conquer C&O Railway's vast repair space. Using force and lots of tools, they work to salvage the steam engine repair plant. S8, Ep11
Splitting Up Jobs. Robert sends Tay and Grayson to salvage on their own, until the crew comes together to help finish the job. Mike and Ted pick up a nautical structure for a client. S8, Ep12
Winter, Lose Or Draw. The worst winter in 100 years is forecast for Nome, Alaska. Shawn chases a jackpot along an ancient riverbed, and Kris goes all-in on new equipment. S10, Ep21
Snow Man's Land. As another snowstorm approaches Nome, Vernon sets up his operation on the promising Claim 56. The Kellys race to get their new equipment on the ice. S10, Ep22
In Western Australia, Alan and Salty hope a local legend will lead them to buried treasure. A new team come face-to-face with the dangers of flying choppers. S9, Ep4
Jurassic River Beast. Fisherman and adventurer, Jeremy Wade, travels to the island of Tasmania in search of a colossal freshwater beast on the verge of disappearing forever. S1, Ep5
Nautical Deathtrap. Freak tides trap Sig in dangerous seas, as Jake battles to get to port. Rick attempts to turn a heart-wrenching tragedy into a triumph for Jacob. S19, Ep22
Wreck In The Shallows. Darrell heads to a shipwreck linked to Gordo's list. He leads his team to the shallows where the tough winds and waves have claimed centuries worth of ships. S2, Ep3
Return Of The Yeti. Josh Gates heads into the Himalayas to obtain scientific evidence of the Yeti. This time his mission is personal and takes him into uncharted territory. S1, Ep1
The Monster And The Mountain. Josh ascends higher into the Himalayas to explore caves. Plus, he investigates the mystical ties the fabled beast has with the Nepalese people. S1, Ep2
Winter's Fury. The Raneys help the Russell family, who are struggling on a failing homestead. The food stocks are low, they don't know how to hunt and their cabin is collapsing. S1, Ep1
Abandoned & Alone. The Raneys help Beth and Mike, who live in a ghost town in Montana. Stalked by a mountain lion, and devoid of any livestock, water or food, survival is a struggle. S1, Ep2
Attack Of The Cacti. After the birth of Daniel's child, the Rookies return to Coober Pedy. Kelly and Al battle a deadly cactus in their hunt for the most valuable opal. S1, Ep4
Brother Vs. Brother. Brothers Peter and Mick Cooke face off in a scrapheap challenge to build a opal hunting machine. And, the rookies resort to night time hunting. S1, Ep5
Zero Hour. King Crab season draws to a close. Casey forces Josh to fish at full throttle on the Cornelia Marie, and Jake takes another turn at the wheel on the Northwestern. S11, Ep8
Hell's Bells. Christmas at sea for the Time Bandit is disturbed when an unhinged deckhand terrorizes the crew. Meanwhile, Jake Anderson awaits the birth of his baby. S11, Ep9
Canyon Of The Apes. Chasing Bigfoot's origin story, Phil and Jessica uncover a rash of recent sightings and bone-chilling new evidence in the Pacific Northwest. S2, Ep7
Smells Like Bigfoot. The team uses new methods to find Bigfoot in NorCal's backcountry, hoping to lure it out of hiding. Russell travels overnight to gather key evidence. S5, Ep6
Marcus and Linden are confronted by a rival gold prospector. The Gold Timers call in a geologist for help, and Robbie storms off the Ferals' lease. S6, Ep9
No Safety In Numbers. Two pairs of survivalists must take on the deadly jungles of Panama side-by-side. But before their 21-day challenge begins, they have a big decision to make. S5, Ep14

Lerner House. The crew travels to Orange, Virginia, to salvage archways, columns and windows from a 1930s brick mansion. Then, Mike and Tay build a coffee table from a door. S8, Ep13
Downtown Kannapolis. Mike and Tay have a consultation for a project from a brewery. But before they can start building they have a salvage job in Kannapolis, North Carolina. S9, Ep1
No Country For Cold Men. Vernon runs out of patience when one of his divers struggles with the freezing temperatures. Plus, Zeke is left frustrated by unexpected flooding. S10, Ep23
Dive Till You Drop. Vernon tries to capitalise on clear weather by sending out two talented divers. Zeke attempts a marathon dive, while Kris has another nightmare day. S10, Ep24
Jacqui and Andrew blaze a new trail into a remote corner of Fish Creek doesn't go according to plan. McGhie's hunch on a new dig site pulls in big gold. S9, Ep5
Toxic Invader. Fisherman and adventurer, Jeremy Wade, travels to western Australia to discover what is wiping out many of the fish in Australia's Fitzroy River. What will he find? S1, Ep6
Everything on the Line. It's a bad start to the crab season as skippers Keith and Phil await medical test results, while repairs to the rest of the boats mean they're all in debt. S5, Ep1
Red Skies in the Morning. A severe storm whips up massive 20ft waves, so most of the boats head for home. But one boat sends out a mayday. Can the coastguard reach it in time? S5, Ep2
Treasure And Tragedy. After finding evidence of a 1700s-era lifeboat near shore, Darrell and the team discover the shipwreck it came from. But a sudden tragedy hits the expedition. S2, Ep4
Out Of Thin Air. Josh's quest takes him from the frozen slopes of Mount Everest to the isolated forests of Bhutan. He uses bait to try and force an encounter with the beast. S1, Ep3
Unmasking The Myth. In the finale, Josh rafts into the remotest corners of Bhutan to capture some of his best evidence yet of the reclusive Yeti. S1, Ep4
Trust Or Die. The Deeters are dog-mushers from Alaska, with a distrust of outsiders. But when disaster strikes, the Raneys must convince them to make drastic changes to their home. S1, Ep3
Under Siege. Josh and Kim raise pigs in Virginia. But with pigs destroying their homestead and predators killing livestock, is it time to let go of their free-range dream? S1, Ep4
Rookies Are The Bomb. Desperate to move more rock, the rookies get a lesson in the dangerous art of bomb-making. Plus, Kelly is forced to sell her precious reserve of stones. S1, Ep6
Cave-Ins And Explosions. With the end of the season approaching, the rookies risk cave-ins at their abandoned mine claim. Deep underground, George is trapped in the blast zone. S1, Ep7
Lunatic Fringe. While Johnathan struggles with a rogue deckhand, skipper Jake prepares for the birth of his baby. Plus, a hydraulic explosion calls Zack's dedication into question. S11, Ep10
New Captain on the Block. While Jake Anderson prepares to captain the Saga for the first time, Captain Andy Hillstrand returns to find the Time Bandit in disarray. S11, Ep11
In St Davids, the crew help an injured fisherman onboard a Belgian trawler. In Dun Laoghaire, a paddleboarder drifts out to sea in an offshore wind. S6, Ep9
In Portrush, the crew rescue a boy in trouble after jumping off rocks. In Eastbourne, the crew help a woman who has drifted out to sea on her paddleboard. S6, Ep10
The Dust Devils' critical water supply runs dry. Jacqui and Andrew find their biggest nugget so far, while the Poseidon Crew are hit by torrential rain. S6, Ep10
